\int_0^{\pi}{x \over{a^2\cos^2 x+b^2\sin^2 x}}dx
{\pi}^2\over{2ab}
\text{As }\int_a^bf(x)dx=\int_a^bf(a+b-x)dx
\displaystyle\sin(\pi-x)=\sin x,\cos(\pi-x)=-\cos x
I=\int_0^\pi{x \over{a^2\cos^2 x+b^2\sin^2 x}}dx=\int_0^\pi\frac{\pi-x}{a^2\cos^2 x+b^2\sin^2 x}dx
I+I=\pi \int_0^\pi\frac1{a^2\cos^2 x+b^2\sin^2 x}dx
=\frac\pi{b^2} \int_0^\pi\frac{\sec^2x}{\left(\frac ab\right)^2+\tan^2 x}dx
\tan x=u
